<TITLE> 3 ex-CID officials get bail in Aug 21 case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 1 (bdnews24.com)Three former CID officials, charged with shielding the real accused in the Aug 21, 2004 grenade attack case and derailing the investigation, secured bail from a Dhaka court on Monday following their surrender on May 12. Metropolitan sessions judge A N M Bashirullah granted them bail on Tk 1 lakh bond each. The three are former CID assistant police superintendents Munshi Atiqur Rahman, Md Abdur Rashid and Md Ruhul Amin. They had previously tried to secure bail after surrendering to the High Court on April 13. The bench of justices M A Wahab Mia and Marjeul Haque at the time directed them to surrender to the trial court instead. CID senior assistant police superintendent Fazlul Kabir filed the case against the three with Paltan Police Station on Mar 29. The case alleged that as successive investigating officers in the grenade attack on an Awami League rally at the Bangabandhu Avenue, the three officials tried to divert the case by compelling innocent witnesses including George Miah to confess in court. They arrested 22 innocent people in total to shield the real accused, the case details said. The grenade attack on the AL rally killed at least 24 people and injured scores, including party chief Sheikh Hasina
